    "synopsis": "Noah Ararat is born into privilege as the 13th prince of an imperial dynasty and granted an existence most can only envy. After all, apart from the access to the empire's finest education and resources, Noah is a reincarnator with the memories of his previous life intact, blessed with an infinite level cap and an elite ability that allows him to utilize his subordinates' skills.  Within the imperial court, however, status alone offers no guarantee of safety. While Noah's overwhelming potential sets him apart from his siblings from the moment he begins his training, it also draws the attention of nobles whose interests extend far beyond governance. Inevitably, Noah must learn to navigate the expectations of royalty and the mechanics of his unusual power, as he realizes that privilege invites control as readily as it grants it.  [Written by MAL Rewrite]",
